<h1>Installation Tutorial</h1>

<p>This is a online image gallery that allows registered users to upload or view images. Oracle database is required for this web app.</p>

<p>Here are the&nbsp;necessary componets to get you up and running:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Setup the lastest version of&nbsp;Tomcat following this link.&nbsp;
	<ul>
		<li><a href="http://www.ntu.edu.sg/home/ehchua/programming/howto/Tomcat_HowTo.html">http://www.ntu.edu.sg/home/ehchua/programming/howto/Tomcat_HowTo.html</a></li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Download our service .zip file (proj1.zip) .</li>
	<li>Unzip or extract the folder inside&nbsp;with a decompression tool (e.g. 7-zip or WinRAR) and place it somewhere you will remember.</li>
	<li>Place the said folder (proj1) in webapps directory.&nbsp; <b>The folder must be name 'proj1'</b></li>
	<li>In proj1/Setup you will find an SQL script (OurSetup.sql) that you must run on the oracle database. (Note: This combines the provided setup_2014.sql with our own modifications).
	<ul>
		<li>Option: we have provided you with a java program located in Setup/Populate.java that will populate the web app with test data. Compile and run this program to populate.</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Our own database credentials are hard coded into the source code. To change the connection details you need to change lines 33-36 of Setup/Populate.java and lines 9-12 of WEB-INF/src/proj1/DatabaseController.java with your own JDBC configuration details, and then recompile those 2 files</li>
	<li>Open a terimal and start Tomcat.</li>
	<li>Open a web broswer. The webapp URL is your usual Tomcat URL with &quot;/proj1&quot; appended at the end.</li>
</ul>

